[3] Venezuela (Carabobo)
Date: Tue 18 Dec 2007
Source: El Nacional [in Spanish trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.el-nacional.com/www/site/detalle_noticia.php?q=nodo/7534>

The most recent figures indicated that in Carabobo state 2750 dengue
cases have been reported, of which 2420 are positive [presumably
laboratory confirmed. - Mod. TY] and 35 await results.
The Governor of Carabobo, Luis Felipe Acosta Carlez, indicated that
the community councils, health committees, PSUV members,
communication media and other public and private institutions must
incorporate themselves in a united front to fight dengue. He issued
this call due to the increase in dengue [cases] and said that he
considers that, "the fight against dengue requires the participation
of all the organized sectors."
Atypical climatic conditions which have affected the entire country
have increased the breeding sites of _Aedes aegypti_, the mosquito
that transmits [dengue virus] in diverse communities in Carabobo,
mainly in the zone north of Valencia's where the greatest number of
[dengue] cases have occurred.
The Governor indicated that printed and audiovisual materials are
available for orientation about the prevention of dengue, treatment
and care of [patients] which this disease deserves. In coming days,
the Carabobo Health Institute will strengthen the [dengue] preventive
campaign in the 14 municipalities of the state and activate the
telephone number so that cases can be reported and the foci of cases
attacked more efficiently.
Humberto Trejo, President of the Health Corporation of Aragua,
although unable to indicate the exact number of dengue cases,
estimates that there have been at least 3000 dengue cases in the
entire state this year [2007]
He indicated that the 5 deaths due to dengue (4 were children) in the
state were caused by dengue [virus] 2, considered by the authorities
to be the most aggressive [virulent] and erratic with a tendency to
rapidly change [from dengue fever] into DHF. Comparing this year
[2007] to 2001, [he said], "there were more [DHF?] cases this year
because [in 2001] the virus was dengue 3, so the mortality [rate] was
not so high". [Because there are significant differences in virulence
both within and among dengue virus serotypes, these types of
generalizations oversimplify relationships of virus type and severity
of disease. Unfortunately there is no satisfactory animal model that
mimics human disease to explore virulence of different dengue virus
types and isolates. - Mod.TY]
Trejo does not discard the proliferation of the mosquito vector of
dengue [virus] _Aedes aegypti_ due to drinking water scarcity, which
obligates citizens to store water in kegs in an inadequate way so
that they become mosquito breeding sites.
Since July [2007], when the epidemiological alert began due to the
increase in [dengue] cases, health authorities have developed plans
to combat the _Aedes aegypti_ mosquito. The [authorities] activated
the plan "Operation Cachivache" which consists of community
elimination of all types of trash which could serve as mosquito breeding sites.
Trejo indicated that "we have achieved important successes related to
the prevention of the disease, although problems continue in the
zones of greatest human population, such as the municipalities south
of Maracay. The jurisdictions where the greatest concentration of
[dengue] cases are found continue to be Girardot and Marino.
--
